of its fiîgures.

207
00:24:37,687 --> 00:24:39,643  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
When the characters
reached the magazine...

208
00:24:39,727 --> 00:24:41,718  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
they were exaggerated...

209
00:24:41,807 --> 00:24:43,957  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
as always happens.

210
00:24:44,047 --> 00:24:47,642  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
This is vintage.

211
00:24:50,407 --> 00:24:52,318  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Well...

212
00:24:57,207 --> 00:24:59,596  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
wrap it up.

213
00:24:59,687 --> 00:25:01,996  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
You've made a considerably
wise decision.

214
00:25:07,207 --> 00:25:09,118  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Well, my kid's gonna go berserk.

215
00:25:12,527 --> 00:25:14,483  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Once again, please?

216
00:25:14,567 --> 00:25:17,240  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
My sonJeb--
it's a gift for him.

217
00:25:17,327 --> 00:25:20,080  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- How old isJeb?
- He's four.

218
00:25:22,967 --> 00:25:24,958  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
No.

219
00:25:25,047 --> 00:25:28,642  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
No, no, no, no, no.

220
00:25:30,087 --> 00:25:32,362  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
You need to go. Now.

221
00:25:34,087 --> 00:25:36,123  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
What'd-What'd I say?

222
00:25:36,207 --> 00:25:39,404  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Do you see any Teletubbies in here?

223
00:25:39,487 --> 00:25:41,443  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Do you see a slender plastic tag
clipped to my shirt...

224
00:25:41,527 --> 00:25:43,597  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
with my name printed on it?

225
00:25:43,687 --> 00:25:46,485  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Did you see a little Asian child with
a blank expression sitting outside...

226
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:50,162  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
in a mechanical helicopter that shakes
when you put quarters in it?

227
00:25:50,247 --> 00:25:53,717  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
No? Well, that's what
you see at a toy store...

228
00:25:53,807 --> 00:25:55,718  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and you must think
you're in a toy store because...

229
00:25:55,807 --> 00:25:59,197  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
you're here shopping
for an infant named Jeb.

230
00:25:59,287 --> 00:26:02,165  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Now, one of us
has made a gross error...

231
00:26:02,247 --> 00:26:05,319  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and wasted the other person's
valuable time.

232
00:26:05,407 --> 00:26:07,443  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
This is an art gallery,
my friend...

233
00:26:07,527 --> 00:26:11,122  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and this is a piece ofart.

234
00:26:25,847 --> 00:26:27,758  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
We're by appointment only.

235
00:26:29,447 --> 00:26:31,961  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- I got a card from this store.
- Congratulations.

236
00:26:32,047 --> 00:26:35,517  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
You have a mailbox.
The exhibition isn't for two weeks.

237
00:26:35,607 --> 00:26:38,326  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
This one was under
the windshield wiper of my car.

238
00:26:41,087 --> 00:26:44,045  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
How certain are you that
you've never taken ill?

239
00:26:44,127 --> 00:26:46,561  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Seventy-fiîve percent.

240
00:26:46,647 --> 00:26:49,957  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Well, that's not
certain at all, is it?

241
00:26:51,327 --> 00:26:54,125  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
That's hole number one.

242
00:26:54,207 --> 00:26:57,279  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I'm going to be extremely skeptical
about all this.

243
00:26:57,367 --> 00:26:59,278  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
About all what?

244
00:27:00,727 --> 00:27:03,799  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I'm assuming you've never been injured.
Would I be wrong in that assumption?

245
00:27:03,887 --> 00:27:05,798  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Dad's been injured.

246
00:27:07,047 --> 00:27:09,925  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Is the child correct?

247
00:27:10,007 --> 00:27:13,966  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Yes, sir. In college,
I was in a car accident.

248
00:27:14,047 --> 00:27:18,723  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Was it serious?
- He couldn't play football any more.

249
00:27:18,807 --> 00:27:20,718  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
That's hole number two.

250
00:27:22,447 --> 00:27:24,358  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
That's a big one.

251
00:27:27,807 --> 00:27:31,595  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Mr Price, can we talk about
the note that you left on my car?

252
00:27:31,687 --> 00:27:34,804  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I've studied the form
ofcomics intimately.

253
00:27:34,887 --> 00:27:36,843  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I've spent a third of my life
in a hospital bed...

254
00:27:36,927 --> 00:27:39,964  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
with nothing else to do but read.

255
00:27:40,047 --> 00:27:41,958  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I believe comics
are our last link...

256
00:27:42,047 --> 00:27:45,596  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
to an ancient way
of passing on history.

257
00:27:45,687 --> 00:27:47,757  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
The Egyptians drew on walls.

258
00:27:47,847 --> 00:27:51,920  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Countries all over the world still pass
on knowledge through pictorial forms.

259
00:27:52,007 --> 00:27:54,077  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I believe comics
are a form of history...

260
00:27:54,167 --> 00:27:57,603  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
that someone somewhere
felt or experienced.

261
00:27:57,687 --> 00:27:59,917  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Then, ofcourse,
those experiences and that history...

262
00:28:00,007 --> 00:28:02,919  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
got chewed up in the commercial
machine, gotjazzed up...

263
00:28:03,007 --> 00:28:05,760  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
made titillating,
cartooned for the sale rack.

264
00:28:07,087 --> 00:28:10,363  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
This city has seen its share
ofdisasters.

265
00:28:10,447 --> 00:28:12,836  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I watched the aftermath
ofthat plane crash.

266
00:28:12,927 --> 00:28:15,361  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I watched the carnage
ofthe hotel fiîre.

267
00:28:15,447 --> 00:28:20,157  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
