a very specifiîc combination ofwords...

268
00:28:20,247 --> 00:28:22,636  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
but they never came.

269
00:28:22,727 --> 00:28:26,322  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Then one day I saw a news story
about a train accident...

270
00:28:26,407 --> 00:28:28,363  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and I heard them.

271
00:28:28,447 --> 00:28:30,438  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
"There is a sole survivor...

272
00:28:30,527 --> 00:28:33,519  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and he is miraculously unharmed."

273
00:28:36,407 --> 00:28:39,717  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I have something called
osteogenesis imperfecta.

274
00:28:39,807 --> 00:28:41,718  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
It's a genetic disorder.

275
00:28:41,807 --> 00:28:43,718  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I don't make a particular
protein very well...

276
00:28:43,807 --> 00:28:46,241  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and it makes my bones
very low in density.

277
00:28:46,327 --> 00:28:48,522  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Very easy to break.

278
00:28:48,607 --> 00:28:51,041  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I've had 54 breaks in my life...

279
00:28:51,127 --> 00:28:55,723  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and I have the tamest version
ofthis disorder, type one.

280
00:28:55,807 --> 00:28:59,356  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
There are type two,
type three, type four.

281
00:28:59,447 --> 00:29:01,358  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Type fours don't last very long.

282
00:29:02,927 --> 00:29:05,805  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
So that's how it popped into my head.

283
00:29:05,887 --> 00:29:08,606  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Ifthere is someone
like me in the world...

284
00:29:08,687 --> 00:29:10,837  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
and I'm at one end
ofthe spectrum...

285
00:29:10,927 --> 00:29:12,883  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
couldn't there be someone else...

286
00:29:12,967 --> 00:29:15,117  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
the opposite of me
at the other end?

287
00:29:15,207 --> 00:29:19,405  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Someone who doesn't get sick, who
doesn't get hurt like the rest of us?

288
00:29:19,487 --> 00:29:23,116  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
And he probably
doesn't even know it.

289
00:29:23,207 --> 00:29:28,201  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
The kind of person
these stories are about.

290
00:29:28,287 --> 00:29:33,202  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
A person put here
to protect the rest of us.

291
00:29:33,287 --> 00:29:35,278  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
To guard us.

292
00:29:37,607 --> 00:29:41,998  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- You think my dad's a real--
- I don't think anything right now.

293
00:29:42,087 --> 00:29:44,442  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
It's a possibility--

294
00:29:44,527 --> 00:29:46,438  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
one with many holes.

295
00:29:49,847 --> 00:29:52,407  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Joseph, don't take
another sip ofthat water.

296
00:29:55,447 --> 00:29:57,438  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Go throw it in the trash.
- But Dad--

297
00:29:57,527 --> 00:29:59,438  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Do it now, please.

298
00:30:08,687 --> 00:30:12,157  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I see guys like you
all the time in my work.

299
00:30:12,247 --> 00:30:15,603  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
You fiînd someone you want
to take advantage of...

300
00:30:15,687 --> 00:30:18,997  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
